Add counts for the same genes

out_l <- list()
for (i in 1:length(dup_linc_genes)) {
  out_l[[i]] <- dup_linc[gene_name == dup_linc_genes[i], ]
  
  for (j in 11:ncol(dup_linc)) {
    out_l[[i]][, j] <- sum(out_l[[i]][, j, with = FALSE])
  }
  out_l[[i]] <- out_l[[i]][gene_length == max(gene_length), ][1, ]
}
out_l <- do.call("rbind",
                 out_l)

out_l

Filter out genes with small number of hits

#Keep the genes with at least 5 out of 92 samples having at least 10 hits each

# Number of samples with at least 10 hits in at least X samples
min_n_hits <- c(1, 5, 10, 20, 50)

l2_l <- list()

for (j in 1:length(min_n_hits)) {
  
  l1_l <- list()
  
  for (i in 1:length(ndx_l)) {
    
    l1_l[[i]] <- data.table(`Min N of hits per sample` = min_n_hits[j],
                            `N samples with min hits or more` = i,
                            `N genes` = sum(rowSums(counts(dds_linc) >= j) >= i))
  }
  l2_l[[j]] <- do.call("rbind",
                       l1_l)
}

ll_l <- do.call("rbind",
                l2_l)
ll_l$`Min N of hits per sample` <- factor(ll_l$`Min N of hits per sample`,
                                          levels = min_n_hits)
ll_l$lw <- 0.5
ll_l$lw[ll_l$`Min N of hits per sample` == 10] <- 1.5

ggplot(ll_l,
       aes(x = `N samples with min hits or more`,
           y = `N genes`,
           group = `Min N of hits per sample`,
           color = `Min N of hits per sample`)) +
  geom_line(linewidth = ll_l$lw) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 10,
             linetype = "dashed",
             color = "red") +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(0, 92, 5)) +
  theme_bw()

keep_l <- rowSums(counts(dds_linc) >= 10) >= 10
sum(keep_l)

dds_linc <- dds_linc[keep_l, ]

p1_l <- ggplot(tmp_l,
               aes(x = `Cohort`,
                   y = log2(Hits + 1))) +
  facet_wrap(~ gene_name,
             scale = "free_y") +
  geom_boxplot(width = 0.3,
               outlier.shape = "") +
  geom_point(aes(fill = AnyDM,
                 group = sample_names),
             size = 2,
             shape = 21,
             alpha = 0.5,
             position = position_dodge(0.3)) +
  scale_y_continuous("Number of hits",
                     breaks = seq(from = 1,
                                  to = 20,
                                  by = 2),
                     labels = (2^seq(from = 1,
                                     to = 20,
                                     by = 2)) - 1) +
  scale_fill_discrete("Any DM",
                      breaks = c(0, 1),
                      labels = c("No",
                                 "Yes")) +
  ggtitle(paste(c("Genes significantly differentially expressed in COVID-19 vs non-COVID patients.",
                  "Difference of the means of log2[hits+1] > 1 and adjusted p-value < 0.05"),

  theme_bw() +

Tests of log2 fold change above or below a threshold (lincRNA)

1.greaterAbs - |β|>x - tests are two-tailed
2.lessAbs - |β|<x - p values are the maximum of the upper and lower tests
3.greater - β>x
4.less - β<−x

The four possible values of altHypothesis are demonstrated in the following code and visually by MA-plots in the following figures.
